and the promises are eternal; the remembrance of benefits with the
'^breadth~,' for breadth is love, out of which all benefits flow;
the contemplation of God's Majesty with the '^height~,' for height is
the infinite power of God; and consideration of His judgments with the
'^depth~,' for 'His judgments are a great deep' (^Ps~.	36.6; ^Rom~.
11.33)], the second of which beholds the 'depth,' that is to say, the
judgments of God. This kind of contemplation 'may violently shock the
